{"cursor":"4973","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n'Pleiotropy' occurs when one gene influences multiple phenotypic traits. Stearns, F. W. (2010). One Hundred Years of Pleitropy: A\nRetrospective. Genetics 186(3):767-773.\nhttp://www.genetics.org/content/186/3/767.abstract Consequently, a\nmutation in a pleiotropic gene may have an effect on some or all traits\nsimultaneously. This can become a problem when selection on one trait favours\none specific version of the gene (allele), while the selection on the other\ntrait favors another allele. The underlying mechanism of pleiotropy in most\ncases is the effect of a gene on metabolic pathways which contribute toward\ndifferent phenotypes.\n","linknr":203,"url":"pleiotropic","recorded":1364118221,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Pleiotropy&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Pleiotropy&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Pleiotropy","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Pleiotropic&redirect=no","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Pleiotropy_(drugs)","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources","/wiki/Wikipedia:INCITE","/wiki/Wikipedi